From: Christian Eggers <ceggers@arri.de>
Date: Tue, 28 Jul 2020 11:29:59 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] eeprom: at25: set minimum read/write access stride to 1
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.9.2
Git-commit: 284f52ac1c6cfa1b2e5c11b84653dd90e4e91de7

commit 284f52ac1c6cfa1b2e5c11b84653dd90e4e91de7 upstream.

SPI eeproms are addressed by byte.

Signed-off-by: Christian Eggers <ceggers@arri.de>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20200728092959.24600-1-ceggers@arri.de
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/misc/eeprom/at25.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/eeprom/at25.c b/drivers/misc/eeprom/at25.c
index ed8d38b09925..e26398fd977e 100644
--- a/drivers/misc/eeprom/at25.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/eeprom/at25.c
@@ -358,7 +358,7 @@ static int at25_probe(struct spi_device *spi)
 	at25->nvmem_config.reg_read = at25_ee_read;
 	at25->nvmem_config.reg_write = at25_ee_write;
 	at25->nvmem_config.priv = at25;
-	at25->nvmem_config.stride = 4;
+	at25->nvmem_config.stride = 1;
 	at25->nvmem_config.word_size = 1;
 	at25->nvmem_config.size = chip.byte_len;
 
